data.description: This Home is on the National Registry of Historic Places. Welcome to the Charles J. Neif House. This Craftsman Style Bungalow Features 4 bedrooms and 2.5 baths. Let's take a walk through. Concrete walkway leads to the covered front porch that expands the front of the home. As you enter to your left is the spacious Living room, spacious formal dining and kitchen. Kitchen has ample tile countertops and cabinet space, small pantry closet. Adjacent to the kitchen is a sunroom sitting area that extends the full length of the back of the home. Basement access is off the kitchen and is used as the laundry room. Main bathroom features a soaking tub surrounded by tile and 2 Pillars, separate shower and double vanity. Main bedroom is spacious and is adjacent to the half bath and spare bedroom downstairs. Upstairs features 2 bedrooms that are spacious with built-ins and seating areas and unique details in workmanship and share a jack and jill bath that has a claw foot tub and shower along with closet space near each vanity. The yard is spacious and has courtyard potential with its variations of Pecan trees and vegetation.
